Blak's black-hole splash uses art and frame data from the milli.nvim project.

Source artwork:
- Project: milli.nvim
- Repository: https://github.com/Amansingh-afk/milli.nvim
- Asset: media/previews/blackhole.gif (kept here as assets/blackhole.gif for reference)
- License: MIT, as stated by the milli.nvim repository.

Source frame data:
- File: lua/blak/splash/frames/blackhole.lua
- Origin: lua/milli/splashes/blackhole.lua on the main branch of milli.nvim, emitted
  by `milli export -t lua` against the GIF above. Copied verbatim apart from a
  header comment that records provenance.

Blak does not vendor any of the milli.nvim runtime — only the data file. The
runtime/animation code in lua/blak/splash/init.lua is Blak's own implementation
of the same anchor-locate-then-paint approach milli uses.
